{"TopicId":193526,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Coordinates and altitude of the surface planet point","CreatedByName":"lolotux","CreatedById":181488,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T16:37:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"lolotux","CreatedById":181488,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T16:37:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello all\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSuper simple and legitimate question (in my opinion) .....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn Kerbin without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Real Solar System (mod)\u0022\u003ERSS\u003C/abbr\u003E without \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Realism Overhaul (mod)\u0022\u003ERO\u003C/abbr\u003E .......\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow to know the coordinates and the altitude of a point?\u003Cbr\u003E\n(without going there)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthank you in advance\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNB: This is to adapt the kscswitch conf file in order to have different KSCs on Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T17:36:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout going there? You may try MechJeb\u0027s landing guidance. You can select a position from map view, afterwards the coordinates and altitude will show up in the Mechjeb Gui.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T18:10:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/KerbNet\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerbNet\u003C/a\u003E will show you the coordinates - and in terrain mode also the altitude - of the position where you put the marker. You will have to have a vessel with KerbNet-view of the place for which you want the information.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lolotux","CreatedById":181488,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T20:23:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779070\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588354575\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Laie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout going there? You may try MechJeb\u0027s landing guidance. You can select a position from map view, afterwards the coordinates and altitude will show up in the Mechjeb Gui.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll try but not really efficient....\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nAt least I will use it !\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779083\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588356656\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/KerbNet\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EKerbNet\u003C/a\u003E will show you the coordinates - and in terrain mode also the altitude - of the position where you put the marker. You will have to have a vessel with KerbNet-view of the place for which you want the information.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yes I will try now !\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lolotux","CreatedById":181488,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T20:54:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a bit laborious .....: /\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laie","CreatedById":110461,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T21:08:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588366477\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181488\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lolotux\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, lolotux said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a bit laborious .....: /\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScansat might help you. You still need to launch a satellite and fast-forward until the entire surface has been mapped, but once the data has been collected, the scansat map and it\u0027s tools may be the best / easiest / most acessible means of finding suitable sites.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-01T21:40:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588366477\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022181488\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022lolotux\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, lolotux said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a bit laborious .....: /\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, well, in real life it\u0027s not all that trivial either.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"lolotux","CreatedById":181488,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-05-03T20:04:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779211\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588369233\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/1/2020 at 11:40 PM, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, well, in real life it\u0027s not all that trivial either.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I found a solution.......\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbal-maps.finitemonkeys.org/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://kerbal-maps.finitemonkeys.org/\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThen play (adapt) the following parameters:\u003Cbr\u003E\nrepositionRadiusOffset = 43\u003Cbr\u003E\nheightMapDeformity = -40\u003Cbr\u003E\nabsoluteOffset = 64\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#dce6f8;color:#1c1e21;font-size:13px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/NathanKell/RealSolarSystem/wiki/PQSCity-and-PQSMod_MapDecalTangent\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/NathanKell/RealSolarSystem/wiki/PQSCity-and-PQSMod_MapDecalTangent\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223779191\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193526\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221588367306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022110461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/1/2020 at 11:08 PM, Laie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScansat might help you. You still need to launch a satellite and fast-forward until the entire surface has been mapped, but once the data has been collected, the scansat map and it\u0027s tools may be the best / easiest / most acessible means of finding suitable sites.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try:!\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nTks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}